# Next.js Development Patterns

## App Router Structure
- **Use App Router** (not Pages Router)
- **File-based routing** in [apps/web-app/src/app/](mdc:apps/web-app/src/app/)
- **Layout components** for shared UI
- **Page components** for route-specific content

## Component Patterns
- **Client Components**: Use 'use client' directive when needed
- **Server Components**: Default for better performance
- **Lazy Loading**: Use Suspense for heavy components
- **Image Optimization**: Use next/image for all images

## Routing Configuration
- **Dynamic Routes**: Use [id] folder structure
- **Nested Routes**: Use folder hierarchy
- **Route Groups**: Use (group) for organization
- **Parallel Routes**: Use @folder for parallel rendering

## Performance Optimization
- **Static Generation**: Prefer static when possible
- **Dynamic Imports**: Use lazy() for code splitting
- **Bundle Analysis**: Monitor bundle size
- **Image Optimization**: Use Next.js Image component

## Configuration Files
- **Next.js Config**: [apps/web-app/next.config.js](mdc:apps/web-app/next.config.js)
- **Tailwind Config**: [apps/web-app/tailwind.config.js](mdc:apps/web-app/tailwind.config.js)
- **TypeScript Config**: [apps/web-app/tsconfig.json](mdc:apps/web-app/tsconfig.json)